The paper deals with graph colouring and probabilistic approaches to bounding the chromatic number and fractional chromatic number. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of probability distributions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
